cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as Named Entity Recognition (NER) and Relation Extraction (RE) in the biomedical domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and its applications. The paper also uses neural architectures for NER, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of multi-task learning and token-level ensembling also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also employs dictionary-based fuzzy and semantic search for Entity Normalization, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with biomedical data, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
